<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIDEO STORE OWNER CONVICTED OF ARSON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The owner of a Kearny Mesa video store that was torched Nov. 8 was found guilty 
Monday of arson in the fire, which caused $135,000 in damage. 
</P>
<P>
Hong Phuc Van, 22, of San Diego hung his head after hearing the verdict. 
Superior Court Judge Milton Milkes set sentencing for April 9. 
</P>
<P>
Attorneys said Van faces up to 12 years in state prison. 
</P>
<P>
An accomplice who was burned in the fire, Dung Diep, 21, of Oxnard, pleaded 
guilty Dec. 14 to arson and will be sentenced March 21. 
</P>
<P>
Diep testified in Van's trial, telling the jury he was to be paid $2,500 for 
setting the fire at the VP Video Store on Mesa College Drive. 
</P>
