<P>
CITY SEEKS TO REPLACE OUTGOING OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Paula city officials are looking for a successor to the assistant city 
administrator, Steve Rogers, who resigned last week. 
</P>
<P>
Rogers accepted a position as assistant to the city administrator in Ann Arbor, 
Mich., City Administrator Bob Livingston said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
After working with Santa Paula for three years, Rogers, 27, was responsible 
primarily for the Personnel Department. His annual salary was about $33,500, 
Livingston said. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for applications is April 6. Rogers is expected to leave the Santa 
Paula job the same day. PSYCHE PASCUAL 
