<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY COUNCIL'S PAY PROPOSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With so many problems facing so many people in our great city, our elected 
leaders are consumed with personal pay increases. I am sure that these leaders 
are well-qualified and, but for their great devotion to service, could secure 
better paying jobs in the private sector. 
</P>
<P>
However, if you will pardon my modesty, I feel equally qualified, equally 
experienced, equally educated and equally ready to match the abilities of any 
of the present servants -- and I would feel fortunate to be able to serve at 
their present wages. 
</P>
<P>
I am also sure that there are in our great community many thousands of greatly 
qualified people who could render greater service to our people if our system 
of election were more democratic. 
</P>
<P>
DAVID ARONOFF 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
