<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BERGER'S HITTING SPARKS UC IRVINE TO 14-1 VICTORY OVER WYOMING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jon Berger hit a three-run home run in the eighth inning as UC Irvine defeated 
Wyoming, 14-1, in a nonconference baseball game Monday in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Berger had three hits and four runs batted in for Irvine (15-8), which has won 
12 of its last 14 games. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters scored five runs in the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
Ed Luna went three for five and drove in a run and Billy Bardens, who had two 
hits and three RBIs, has a hit in each of the Anteaters' last 11 games. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Huber (3-0) allowed three hits and struck out seven to earn the victory. 
Wyoming is 7-7. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 5, Kansas 1 -- The host Anteaters, ranked ninth in the nation, won 
five of six singles matches and doubles matches weren't played. Irvine's Trevor 
Kronemann, ranked No. 25 nationally, defeated No. 35 John Falbo, 6-2, 6-7, 6-3, 
in No. 1 singles. Irvine improved to 9-5; Kansas dropped to 5-7. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
Christ College Irvine 15-15, U.S. Coast Guard Academy 0-0 -- Michelle Vail 
pitched a no-hitter and struck out nine in the first game of doubleheader for 
host Christ College (12-7). 
</P>
<P>
Kathy Carroll went six for nine with two RBIs and De Brunk was five for eight 
with seven RBIs for Chris College. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 3, George Mason 0 -- Scott Recknor had 17 kills and 14 digs as host 
Irvine (5-10) won, 15-8, 15-9, 15-10. 
