<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: ATI MEDICAL'S PROFIT RISES 60% IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATI Medical Inc., a Glendale company that rents medical equipment to hospitals, 
said its fiscal second-quarter profit jumped 60% from a year earlier on a 29% 
increase in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter that ended Jan. 31, ATI's net income rose to $873,479 from 
$547,411 a year ago, while its revenue climbed to $12.6 million from $9.8 
million. 
</P>
<P>
For the first half of its fiscal year, ATI's profit more than doubled to $1.67 
million from $757,254, and its six-month revenue was up 32% to $24.1 million 
from $18.3 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
