<TEXT>
<P>
The ceiling of a food shop collapsed in the Ansonia Hotel on Manhattan's Upper 
West Side, killing a woman and injuring 12 other people, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A Fire Department spokesman said the building was evacuated after the collapse 
in the Croissant &amp; Co. shop on the ground floor of the 17-story hotel. City 
Buildings Commissioner Charles Smith said that the ceiling was old and ornate, 
and a new ceiling suspended from it apparently had added too much weight. 
Police said those inside were briefly trapped in the debris, and three of those 
hurt suffered head injuries. 
