<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Semiconductor Corp.: The computer chip maker said it lost $10.2 
million in its third quarter, compared to a $44.6-million loss in the same 
period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Sales rose 6.6% to $404.3 million. The Santa Clara, Calif., firm said the third 
quarter "is historically a challenging one for us, incorporating a seasonal 
slowdown in sales, along with the annual holiday shutdown of our production 
facilities." The results were helped by the reversal of $4.6 million in 
one-time costs originally set aside to pay for the closing of a Danbury, Conn., 
plant. The firm also had $6.7 million in non-recurring credits. 
</P>
