<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Apple to Buy Back Shares: Apple Computer Inc. announced that it would buy back 
up to 5 million shares of its stock, which would represent 4% of the firm's 
125.2 million shares outstanding. 
</P>
<P>
The Cupertino, Calif., company said its board approved the plan because of its 
strong financial outlook. But industry analysts were unimpressed, saying that 
Apple, beset by a computer-buying slowdown and a dearth of new products, was 
clearly on the defensive. Since July, 1986, Apple has repurchased a total of 20 
million common shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
