<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARNESS DISPUTE IS HEARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Both sides in the dispute over the disqualification of about 150 harness-racing 
drivers at Los Alamitos presented their case before an administrative law judge 
during a six-hour hearing Monday in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
The judge, Amanda Behe, may submit her opinion in time for the California Horse 
Racing Board meeting in Albany on March 30. 
</P>
<P>
The board can either accept or reject Behe's decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
