<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beach Boys Fuel Up for Concert Tour: Texaco is sending out good vibrations to 
"Beach Boys" fans by sponsoring a free 10-city concert tour starting May 1 at 
the San Diego Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
No tickets will be sold for the concert; instead, those who want to attend can 
try to win tickets by playing a scratch-off game at Texaco stations. The Second 
Harvest National Food Bank Network will also give away tickets in exchange for 
donations of perishable food. The tour makes stops in Phoenix, Seattle and New 
York. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
