<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Most Wanted' Show Prompts Arrest: A murder suspect was in custody in Los 
Angeles on Monday after an anonymous caller telephoned police following Sunday 
night's episode of "America's Most Wanted." Based on information provided by 
the caller, Segundo Matias, 27, was arrested about 10:30 p.m. Sunday by 
officers on a murder warrant issued nearly two years ago in Honolulu, said Sgt. 
Mike Evers. BETH KLEID 
</P>
