<P>
BLUE JAYS RENEW STIEB'S OPTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TORONTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Blue Jays today exercised the 1990 option in the contract of right-hander 
Dave Stieb for $1.6 million. 
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of Stieb's contract, signed in March, 1985, the team had until 
Thursday to renew his option for 1990 or buy out the contract for $800,000. 
</P>
<P>
His salary for the 1990 season would have been guaranteed automatically if 
Stieb had pitched in 225 or more innings in 1989, but he pitched 206 2/3 
innings last season. 
</P>
<P>
Stieb was 17-8 in 1989 with a 3.35 earned-run average. He is the club's 
all-time leader in several categories: victories (148), strikeouts (1,432) and 
complete games (99). 
</P>
